      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To find the total impedance ($Z$) of your series RL circuit, you need to treat resistance ($R$) and inductive reactance ($X_L$) as vectors, not just adding them up. The formula for total impedance is $\\sqrt{R^2 + X_L^2}$. Simply plug in your values: $Z = \\sqrt{50^2 + 30^2}$ to get the final answer. This calculation will give you the total opposition to the current flow in the circuit.",
